content: Woo Hoo!
I think I am going to wait all day for them.
Much better than I expected when I saw them at 'Roo. Great fun rock and roll band.
Hawaii-based party DJ.

The second best Irish punk rock out there. Look for the crowd to explode during their closing song, a tweaked cover song from the Kingston Trio renamed as "Skinhead on the MTA".

Be very careful wearing glasses to this show.
Goth electronica. Bauhaus with a drum machine.
Happy pop music. All their videos seem to be shot outside during the day. I'm not sure these guys understand what a vampire is.
The Violent Femmes are a New Wave band. They are not a punk rock band.

Maynard James Keenan's "lounge act" side project. Pretty random eclectic group. Another rating change after looking at the mock schedule. There is no practical way I will miss this unless it is up against something else I really want to see.

The best punk rock band in Southern Califronia. I hated their last album, but the last few times I've seen them, they have only played the stuff I like.

Even with no Rolling Stones at Coachella, look for Social Distortion to tear it up with their cover of "Under My Thumb".
One of my favorite Coachella memories is walking through the crowd during New Order to be at the front of the Main Stage for NIN. I must have pissed off over a hundred indie rockers that night.
Radio-friendly anthemic indie rock. Caught these guys at the DC Chili Cook-Off, where they blew the headliners away. Well worth a listen.
DIIV strikes me as the epitome of the late afternoon Coachella band. Listening to them, I can almost a feel breeze picking up, as the sun sets.
Clean, radio-friendly sound with some prog elements. Could be a sleeper hit.
Electronica. Very cool sound. Not to be missed.
Britpop. Full of drama, which could make for a good stage show.
Reunited goth-rock stalwarts with a lot of world music influences. They seem to hate each other, so maybe it's all for the money. And they can't afford the full band, so it's mostly electronic.
Synthesizers meet dimestore torch singer.
Complex electronica. Varies in tempo, style, rhtythym, sound.
Old school punk legends.
